  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 17, 58, 15.555057}", 
    "history" -> {"12", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"linear algebra", "tensor analysis", "direct product"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Tensorize[m] gives the tensor product form of the matrix m. The matrix m \
is supposed to be the matrix representation of a multi-qubit system and hence \
a 2^n*2^n square matrix, where n is the number of qubits. Tensorize[v] gives \
the tensor product form of the vector v. The vector v is supposed to be the \
column-vector representation of a multi-qubit system and hence a column \
vector of size 2^n. Tensorize[m | v, {d1, d2, ...}] assumes the subsystems \
are associated with the Hilbert spaces with dimensions d1, d2, ....", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "Tensorize", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
    "Tensorize", "type" -> "Symbol", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/ref/Tensorize"}},
